topic.title: Firmware Logging Settings

body.p: The Log Setting Block allows users to define a separate log filter severity level for each firmware module and set the log entry count for firmware log module. By default, the entries are saved into an internal RAM. They can also be saved into external RAM by defining the address of the external RAM. A separate log filter level can be set for up to 16 modules, the other modules use the global filter level. If the Flash Saving Enable bit is set as "1", the log entries are saved into Flash when a fatal error happens.

body.p: Log Severity Level(0x0 ~ 0x5) is defined as below table. Setting a module's log severity level will make the events with higher log severity level logged. For example, if a module with filter severity level 3(medium), then the events with severity level 1(highest), 2(high), 3(medium) will be logged into RAM.

row.entry: Memory corruption, watchdog timeout, FW assertion, SPI multi-bits ECC errors and CPU related exceptions.
Unexpected or critical code path in PSC module or PTD module
Low level debug events (warning, this may fill the log ram buffer quickly)
